# MyDSP UI — form & modal conventions

Match the Jobs section (`JobFormModal`) for all data-entry UI across MyDSP.

## Never

- Do not use `window.prompt()`, `window.confirm()`, `window.alert()`, or native browser dialogs for create/edit/delete flows.
- Use `ConfirmDialog` from `src/components/ui/Modal.tsx` for destructive confirms.
- Do not invent one-off input styles per page.

## Modal shell

```tsx
<div className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 flex items-center justify-center z-50 p-4 overflow-y-auto">
  <div className="surface rounded-xl max-w-3xl w-full max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto my-8">
    <div className="sticky top-0 surface border-b border-border p-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <h2 className="text-xl font-bold">Title</h2>
      {/* close btn-ghost */}
    </div>
    <form className="p-6 space-y-6">…</form>
  </div>
</div>
```

Use `max-w-lg` for short forms (e.g. list name); `max-w-3xl` for multi-section forms.

## Sections & fields

- Group related fields under `<h3 className="font-bold mb-3">Section</h3>`.
- Layout: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4`.
- Labels: `block text-xs text-text-subtle mb-1` with `*` for required.
- Inputs/selects/textareas: `w-full px-3 py-2 bg-surface-hover border border-border rounded text-sm`.
- Footer actions: Cancel `btn-ghost` + Submit `btn-primary` in a top-bordered row.

## Page filters

Reuse the same label + input classes for search/sort/filter bars (tight, labeled, grid — not floating unlabeled chips).

## Theme tokens

Prefer design tokens (`surface`, `surface-hover`, `border`, `text-subtle`, `accent`, `btn-primary`) over hard-coded colors.
